titles: An impartial consideration of those speeches, which pass under the name of the five Jesuits lately executed viz. [brace] Mr. Whitebread, Mr. Harcourt, Mr. Gawen, Mr. Turner, and Mr. Fenwick : in which it is proved, that according to their principles, they not only might, but also ought, to die after that manner, with solemn protestation of their innocency.
author: Williams, John, 1636?-1709.
notes: Attributed to Williams by Wing and NUC pre-1956 imprints.
Reproduction of original in the Union Theological Seminary Library, New York.
